We'd like to record, acknowledge, and thank the following people for
their contributions to epydemic:

- Saray Shai (the original inspiration)
- Peter Mann (lots of maths and experiments)
- Martynas Noreika (exploring parallel implementations)
- Mike Pitcher (applications in TB modelling)
- Aleksejs Sazonovs (applications in zoonotic disease modelling)
- Oleksander Konovalov (continuous integration)
- Liberty Askew (vaccination and opinion dynamics models)
- Luke Beardsmore (explored GPU implementation)
- Hamish Finn (explored the subtleties of synchronous dymamics
  event orderings)
- Martin Prestage (discovered more complicated Newman-Ziff use
  cases that led to progressively building the network as it
  percolates)